<li id="cite_note-Lamb-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Lamb_16-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFHorace_Lamb1916">Horace Lamb (1916). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=OztMAAAAMAAJ&amp;pg=PA341&amp;dq=%22dynamical+tide%22&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0#PPA339,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=OztMAAAAMAAJ&amp;pg=PA341&amp;dq=%22dynamical+tide%22&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0#PPA339,M1" rel="nofollow">Hydrodynamics</a></i> (4th Edition ed.). Cambridge University Press. pp.&#160;339. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521458684" class="internal">ISBN 0521458684</a>. <a href="/wiki/Online_Computer_Library_Center" title="Online Computer Library Center">OCLC</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/oclc/30070401+31079426+33629948" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/oclc/30070401+31079426+33629948" rel="nofollow">30070401 31079426 33629948</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=OztMAAAAMAAJ&amp;pg=PA341&amp;dq=%22dynamical+tide%22&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0#PPA339,M1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=OztMAAAAMAAJ&amp;pg=PA341&amp;dq=%22dynamical+tide%22&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0#PPA339,M1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=OztMAAAAMAAJ&amp;pg=PA341&amp;dq=%22dynamical+tide%22&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0#PPA339,M1</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Hydrodynamics&amp;rft.aulast=Horace+Lamb&amp;rft.au=Horace+Lamb&amp;rft.date=1916&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B339&amp;rft.edition=4th+Edition&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/30070401+31079426+33629948&amp;rft.isbn=0521458684&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DOztMAAAAMAAJ%26pg%3DPA341%26dq%3D%2522dynamical%2Btide%2522%26lr%3D%26as_brr%3D0%23PPA339%2CM1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Tide"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Americana-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Americana_17-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFRollin_A_Harris1918">Rollin A Harris (1918). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=CF4fijqC9GgC&amp;pg=RA1-PA613&amp;dq=%22equilibrium+tide%22&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0#PRA1-PA614,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=CF4fijqC9GgC&amp;pg=RA1-PA613&amp;dq=%22equilibrium+tide%22&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0#PRA1-PA614,M1" rel="nofollow">The Encyclopedia Americana: A Library of Universal Knowledge</a></i>. Encyclopedia Americana. Article on Tides, pp. 613–614<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=CF4fijqC9GgC&amp;pg=RA1-PA613&amp;dq=%22equilibrium+tide%22&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0#PRA1-PA614,M1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=CF4fijqC9GgC&amp;pg=RA1-PA613&amp;dq=%22equilibrium+tide%22&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0#PRA1-PA614,M1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=CF4fijqC9GgC&amp;pg=RA1-PA613&amp;dq=%22equilibrium+tide%22&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0#PRA1-PA614,M1</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Encyclopedia+Americana%3A+A+Library+of+Universal+Knowledge&amp;rft.aulast=Rollin+A+Harris&amp;rft.au=Rollin+A+Harris&amp;rft.date=1918&amp;rft.pages=Article+on+Tides%2C+pp.+613%E2%80%93614&amp;rft.pub=Encyclopedia+Americana&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DCF4fijqC9GgC%26pg%3DRA1-PA613%26dq%3D%2522equilibrium%2Btide%2522%26lr%3D%26as_brr%3D0%23PRA1-PA614%2CM1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Tide"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-difference-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-difference_18-0" title="">^</a></b> Two points on either side of the Earth sample the imposed gravity at two nearby points, effectively providing a finite difference of the gravitational force that varies as the inverse square of the distance. The derivative of 1/<i>r</i><sup>2</sup>, with <i>r</i> = distance to originating body, varies as the inverse cube.</li>
<li id="cite_note-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-19" title="">^</a></b> Hypothetically, if the ocean were a constant depth, there were no land, and the Earth did not rotate, high water would occur as two bulges in the height of the oceans, one facing the Moon and the other on the opposite side of the Earth, facing away from the Moon. There would also be smaller, superimposed bulges on the sides facing toward and away from the Sun.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Munk1998-20"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Munk1998_20-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFMunk.2C_W.1998">Munk, W. (1998), "Abyssal recipes II: energetics of tidal and wind mixing", <i>Deep Sea Research Part I Oceanographic Research Papers</i> <b>45</b>: 1977, <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016%2FS0967-0637%2898%2900070-3" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016%2FS0967-0637%2898%2900070-3" rel="nofollow">10.1016/S0967-0637(98)00070-3</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Abyssal+recipes+II%3A+energetics+of+tidal+and+wind+mixing&amp;rft.jtitle=Deep+Sea+Research+Part+I+Oceanographic+Research+Papers&amp;rft.aulast=Munk%2C+W.&amp;rft.au=Munk%2C+W.&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.volume=45&amp;rft.pages=1977&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1016%2FS0967-0637%2898%2900070-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Tide"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Ray1996-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Ray1996_21-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFRay.2C_R._D.1996">Ray, R. D. (1996), "Detection of tidal dissipation in the solid Earth by satellite tracking and altimetry", <i>Nature</i> <b>381</b>: 595, <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1038%2F381595a0" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1038%2F381595a0" rel="nofollow">10.1038/381595a0</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Detection+of+tidal+dissipation+in+the+solid+Earth+by+satellite+tracking+and+altimetry&amp;rft.jtitle=Nature&amp;rft.aulast=Ray%2C+R.+D.&amp;rft.au=Ray%2C+R.+D.&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.volume=381&amp;rft.pages=595&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1038%2F381595a0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Tide"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
